<dl id="s14036c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14036c">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s14all.htm#s14036c">sector 36(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> toothache &mdash; rheumatism</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Most truly I have told the reader, that not any search after pleasure, but mere extremity of pain from rheumatic toothache&mdash;this and nothing else was it that first drove me into the use of opium. Coleridge&apos;s bodily affliction was simple rheumatism. Mine, which intermittently raged for ten years, was <mark>rheumatism in the face combined with toothache</mark>. <small> Thomas De Quincey, <a name="TDQC" href="/udra/udex.htm#TDQC"><cite title="source">Confessions of an English Opium-Eater</cite></a> (1909), 15</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
